Whilſt I have been thus reaſoning of Judgement to come, poſſibly ſome Felix may tremble, the thoughts of Hell may have kindled ſome affection towards heaven, and he whom the love of Chriſt could not conſtrain, yet the terror of the Lord may have almoſt perſwaded to be a Chriſtian;


                        〈 in non-Latin alphabet 〉
                      Cyr. Chat. 15. p. 389. being fore-warned, he may deſire to flee from this wrath to come. Such I ſhall ſend to John Baptiſt for direction in this caſe, Mat. 3.8. Bring forth fruits worthy of amendment of life: Avoid thoſe ſins which do in a principal manner lead to theſe chambers of death, and bring forth the fruits of Holineſs, the end whereof is Eternal Life.
